RIVER-TORTOISES.

The rivers, lakes, and strealnS, abound in tortoiseS‚ but not of that kind the shells of which are valuable in Europe, and fit for work- ing. No sooner did we cast a hook into the river than a tortoise would bite, but was always rejected by us; for in the greater part of Para- guay these animals are eaten neither by Spani- ards nor Indians. The only useful part of tor- toises in Paraguay is their great shells, which are used for pots and plates by the common people.
